    "department": "Corporate",
    "description": "Riveron is seeking a Senior Associate – Resource Management professional to support data-driven resource planning and operational insight across the firm. This role is focused on maintaining high-quality resource data, producing accurate and actionable reporting, and enabling leadership decision-making through strong analytical and systems expertise. If you are detail-oriented, analytically minded, and excel at managing complex data in a fast-paced environment, we’d love to hear from you.\n\nWho You Are\n\nYou are a highly organized and detail-driven professional with experience in resource management, workforce analytics, or operations, ideally within a professional services or consulting environment. You have a strong aptitude for working with data, systems, and reporting tools, and take pride in accuracy, consistency, and data integrity. You are comfortable operating in dynamic environments where priorities evolve, and you maintain quality and precision even under tight timelines. You bring strong analytical thinking, clear communication skills, and a proactive mindset that allows you to translate data into meaningful insights for business leaders. You are collaborative and reliable, known for follow-through, discretion, and sound judgment when working with sensitive people and business data.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nMaintain and manage resource management databases and deployment tools, ensuring data accuracy, completeness, and consistency across systems. Produce regular and ad hoc reporting related to utilization, capacity, demand, pipeline, and deployment trends to support business planning and leadership decisions. Analyze resource data to identify trends, risks, and opportunities related to workforce capacity, utilization, and forecasting. Support leadership with data-driven insights by preparing dashboards, summaries, and clear reporting outputs that enable effective decision-making. Conduct ongoing data quality reviews, identify discrepancies, and proactively resolve issues to improve reporting reliability and system integrity. Partner with stakeholders to understand reporting needs and translate business questions into structured analyses and actionable outputs. Maintain advanced proficiency in Excel and reporting tools (such as PowerBI), including pivot tables and lookups. Support continuous improvement of resource management processes, reporting standards, and documentation to enhance efficiency, accuracy, and scalability.\n\nRequired Qualifications:\n\n - Over 5 years of total work experience; ideally with more than 3 years of experience in operations or resource management, preferably in a professional services environment.\n\n - Strong proficiency in English communication (verbal and written).\n\n - High attention to detail and strong organizational skills.\n\n - Proven ability to manage multiple priorities and deliver results in a fast-paced environment.\n\n - Executive presence and strong interpersonal skills; comfortable interacting with senior leadership and staff.\n\n - Proficiency with Microsoft Excel (including pivot tables and VLOOKUPs).\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\n - Proficiency with PowerBI.\n\n - Experience advisory/consulting practices.\n\n - Familiarity with resource or workforce planning tools and analytics.\n\nAbout Riveron:\n\nAt Riveron, we partner with clients—from global multinationals to high-growth private entities—to solve complex finance challenges, guided by our DELTA values: Drive, Excellence, Leadership, Teamwork, and Accountability. Our entrepreneurial culture thrives on collaboration, diverse perspectives, and delivering exceptional outcomes. We are committed to fostering growth, both for our clients and our people, through mentorship, integrity, and a client-centric approach. This inclusive environment offers flexibility, progressive benefits, and meaningful opportunities for impactful work that supports well-being in and out of the office.\n\nCheck us out on social media:\n\nLinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/riveron/life/culture/ Glassdoor https://www.glassdoor.com/Photos/Riveron-Office-Photos-E672242.htm Instagram https://www.instagram.com/riveronconsulting/ Facebook https://www.facebook.com/RiveronConsulting/\n\nRiveron Consulting is an Equal Opportunity Employer and believes that we are stronger together through our diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other characteristic protected by law.\n\nFull time roles are eligible for a full range of benefits including medical, dental, and vision insurance, 401(k) with company match, and PTO. A complete description of all available benefits can be found at Riveron's Benefits page at https://riveron.com/riveron-life/. Contract roles are not eligible for benefits.\n\n\nFRAUD ALERT\n\nPlease beware of fraudulent schemes or impersonations when going through the job application process. A Riveron employee will never recruit via text or extend unsolicited employment offers. Additionally, a Riveron employee will never ask you to exchange money or purchase anything as part of the recruiting process.\n\n\nWE MAY USE ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) TOOLS TO SUPPORT PARTS OF THE HIRING PROCESS, SUCH AS REVIEWING APPLICATIONS, ANALYZING RESUMES, OR ASSESSING RESPONSES. THESE TOOLS ASSIST OUR RECRUITMENT TEAM BUT DO NOT REPLACE HUMAN JUDGMENT. FINAL HIRING DECISIONS ARE ULTIMATELY MADE BY HUMANS. IF YOU WOULD LIKE MORE INFORMATION ABOUT HOW YOUR DATA IS PROCESSED, PLEASE CONTACT US.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
